  "text": "The Grafana dashboard JSON schema version migration pipeline is implemented across multiple backend Go packages and a TypeScript frontend mirror. The system architecture consists of the following key components:\n\n## Backend Migration Runner\nThe `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/migrate.go` file contains the core migration orchestrator with the `Migrate()` function that executes the migration pipeline. It calls `Initialize()` to set up the migration system with the registry of all schema version functions. The runner implements a comprehensive migration flow: cleaning dashboard properties, tracking original transformations, applying frontend defaults (via `applyFrontendDefaults()`), ensuring unique panel IDs, validating minimum version, and executing the sequential migration pipeline.\n\n## Migration Registry\nThe `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go` file defines the `GetMigrations()` function that returns a map[int]SchemaVersionMigrationFunc, mapping schema versions 2-42 to their corresponding migration functions. Each version (v2, v3, v4, ..., v42) has a dedicated migration function that modifies the dashboard JSON structure. The type `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` is defined as `func(context.Context, map[string]interface{}) error`.\n\n## Individual Migration Steps\nEach schema version from 2 to 42 has a dedicated migration file:\n- V2 (apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v2.go) migrates legacy services.filter structure\n- V3-V5 handle early schema changes\n- V16 (apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v16.go) performs the critical grid layout migration\n- V33 and V36 handle datasource reference migrations\n- V38 (apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v38.go) migrates table display modes\n- V39-V42 handle final schema refinements\n\nThese migration files implement the actual transformation logic for each schema version.\n\n## Shared Utilities\nThe migration system uses shared utility functions:\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migration_utils.go` provides safe extraction functions (GetStringValue, GetBoolValue, GetIntValue, GetFloatValue, ConvertToInt, ConvertToFloat)\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/datasource_utils.go` handles datasource-specific transformations\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/errors.go` defines error types\n\n## Frontend Defaults Application\nThe `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/frontend_defaults.go` file implements `applyFrontendDefaults()` which replicates DashboardModel constructor defaults from the TypeScript frontend, ensuring backend migrations produce identical results to the frontend.\n\n## API Conversion Layer\nThe `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/conversion/` directory contains API version conversion functions that bridge dashboard object models between different API versions (v0alpha1, v1beta1, v2alpha1, v2beta1). The `conversion.go` file's `RegisterConversions()` function registers all conversion functions in the Kubernetes scheme.\n\n## Frontend TypeScript Mirror\nThe `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts` file implements the `DashboardMigrator` class that mirrors the backend migration logic on the frontend. It exports `DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION = 42` (the latest version) and implements the `updateSchema()` method that executes individual schema migrations (versions 2-42) with the same logic as the backend.\n\n## Final Version\nThe schema version 42 is designated as the FINAL version for the v1 dashboard API. No new schema migrations should be added beyond this version. For panel-specific migrations, they should be implemented in individual panel plugin migration handlers instead.\n\nThe complete migration pipeline ensures that legacy dashboards are reliably transformed to the current schema version through sequential application of all necessary migrations, with perfect parity between frontend and backend migration logic."
}

